search capacity in that country specifically through research projects conducted by trainees that are targeted to address chinese health policy priorities through a collaboration between the china health economics institute beijing and chp pcor's center for demography and economics of health and aging the project aims to 1 provide a us based training program for new health services researchers from china 2 provide joint us chinese mentoring for trainee research performed as part of a degree granting program in china and 3 augment training and research opportunities in china on health services research through seminars conferences and meetings contact wei yu funding provided by national institutes of health publications private and public cross subsidization financing beijing's health insurance reform ming wu y xin h wang wei yu health policy vol 72 1 2005 html+ events & presentations factors influencing healthcare utilization of the elderly in urban beijing china december 15 2004 special seminar ming wu feasibility study for establishing a multi tier healthcare system for the elderly in china research in progress seminar research in progress seminar guohong li search chp search within everything courses events fellowships news op eds people publications research other pages research news researchers present work meet with global collaborators at health economics conference july 29 2005 chpintl news support map & directions contact rss+ rss xml feeds freeman spogli institute for international studies encina hall 616 serra st stanford ca 94305 6055 tel 650 736 0815 fax 650 725 2592 mail code 6055
